(69,	68,	'shop_vendor',	'<b>Born and raised</b> in <strong>New Zealand</strong>, Chef and lover of living a passionate healthy life, Rebecca has spent the last 12 years travelling and working around the globe immersing herself in culture, food and the colours of the world.\r\n\r\nGaining her experience as a Private Chef aboard luxury yachts throughout the Caribbean, Mediterranean, USA, Pacific and North Africa, to finally settle on the shores of Sydney, Australia.\r\n\r\nIntuitive. Original. Creative. Rebecca\'s three principles to her service. Rebecca has a wealth of knowledge on healthy cooking and integrating wellness into life to create balance and harmony. She aspires to conjure up exciting meals within dietary constraints to allow her clients to see there are still many \'haves\' vs \'have nots\'.\r\n\r\nHaving studied Nutrition &amp; Wellness with IIN in New York City and working for clients with dietary needs for over 10 years, she specializes in Dairy, Gluten &amp; Refined Sugar or Sugar Free Diets. Abundant with knowledge on Vegetarian &amp; Vegan diets plus a wide variety of experience with Super Foods!\r\n\r\nRebecca can also support you if you have been recently diagnosed with Digestive Issues, an Auto Immune Disease, Arthritis, Diabetes, Food Allergies, Airborne Allergies, Cardiovascular Disease or Cancer, she will assist you to integrate your new diet into your life with ease and a fresh perspective.\r\n\r\nRebecca spreads her love across the fields of Wellness &amp; Food Coaching, as an Organic &amp; Dietary Chef, Conscious Cooking Teacher &amp; Food Stylist.',	0,	2),
