(99,	96,	'shop_vendor',	'15 years of experience as a representative player and subsequent coach of Europe I played the Beachvolleyball World Tour Series and representative national team of Czech Republic. Lessons are on a NSW reptiles, especially Eastern Suburbs beaches (beach volleyball), Parks on Sydney (fitness and weight training). After the agreement may be training and in other locations!',	0,	1),
(100,	97,	'shop_vendor',	'Holistic approach to health - Personal Training, Nutrition, Massage, Relaxation, Hypnosis. Personalized, goal-orientated and effective.\r\n\r\nAreas of expertise:\r\n\r\n- Personal Training - Endurance, Strength &amp; Conditioning, Weight loss, Rehabilitation\r\n- Massage\r\n- Nutrition\r\n- Relaxation\r\n- Dorn Breuss spine &amp; craniosacral therapy\r\n- Hypnosis',	0,	1),
(103,	100,	'shop_vendor',	'Bondi based personal training, specialising in boxing!\r\nAffordable and fun. for all ages and types.',	0,	1),
(104,	101,	'shop_vendor',	'Hey there to everyone, if you are wanting to get fit and healthy during, Summer, Winter or Spring and want 4 FREE Personal Training Sessions to try before you sign up!!!!\r\nThen Come to The Workout Club, Darlinghurst\r\n\r\nAbout Me :)\r\nTo be Honest I never was that fit as a kid, I was pretty chubby and not fit at all when I was 9 years old. that was until I started Teakwondo :)\r\n\r\nand now today i\'m now a qualified Personal Trainer who has train in various Marital Arts including\r\n* 2nd Dan Black Belt in Teawondo\r\n*Mixed Martial Arts\r\n*Mauy Thai\r\n*Ju-Jitsu\r\n\r\nWe offer to you the Best Personal Trainers in Sydney where we give the Clients what they want from Weight lifting, Cross Training, Boxing, Cardio and the list goes on, Plus a New GYM will Be Opening soon thats BIGGER AND BETTER!!!!',	0,	1),
(105,	102,	'shop_vendor',	'PERSONAL TRAINER\r\n\r\nLiam has been a PERSONAL TRAINER and strength &amp; conditioning coach for five years in the Bondi Beach area. Originally from the UK, Liam has spent the last 14 years living the dream and surfing Bondi’s waves. As a regular at the famed North Bondi rope climb, and after many years volunteering as a Bondi lifesaver, he has developed to become a local fitness identity.\r\n\r\nThroughout his life Liam constantly challenges himself with a wide variety of sporting activities, from basketball to boxing, to Greco Roman Wresting. His next challenge is to compete in Olympic Weight Lifting as a Master – watch this space!\r\n\r\nAfter years of training, Liam’s sports proficiency, and additional experience as a fitness model enables him to channel his knowledge into PERSONAL TRAINING for clients. He has a passion to help people to effectively achieve the results they are striving for, whether the desire is aesthetic, for performance, or both.\r\n\r\nQUALIFICATIONS\r\n\r\nCertification 3 FITNESS INSTRUCTOR\r\nCertification 4 PERSONAL TRAINER\r\nDIPLOMA of fitness Exercise specialist\r\nASCA Strength &amp; Conditioning coach level 1\r\nOlder adults and Children\'s trainer\r\nO of E Trinity flexibility trainer\r\nQualified Lifesaver\r\nQualified “Thump” Boxing instructor\r\nAdvanced first aid\r\nFully Insured Fitness Professional',	0,	1),
(106,	103,	'shop_vendor',	'As a fully qualified personal trainer and an international athlete, and I\'m offering you an enjoyable, effective and safe personal training service! I bring the equipment so you can train from home, outdoors, or at the fantastic centennial health club- as my client I will cover your entrance!\r\n\r\nI have enjoyed over 5 years experience as a personal trainer, with all abilities and ages of people. I can particularly help you if you are looking to improve sports/ running/surfing conditioning, strength, weightloss or rehab. Making you look, feel and function better is my passion.',	0,	1),
(107,	104,	'shop_vendor',	'Hello, My name’s Yazmina and I’m from spain. I have 11 years experience in fitness and I’m very passionate about changing people’s lifestyle. If you want to lose weight, tone up or keep fit, I can help you. \r\n\r\nI also offer measurements of body composition (Body mass index, %Body Fat, %Muscle, etc.) It cost $20 and I recommended to do it every 4 or 6 weeks. \r\n\r\nDIETS: \r\nI can prepare a plan/diet for you and the price is $100. \r\nI can prepare some different diets until get your goal (2 or 3 differents will be enough every a few weeks). \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEducation \r\n\r\nPersonal Trainer level I y II (Federación Madrileña de gimnasia). \r\nNutrition and Sports supplementation (Federación Madrileña de gimnasia) \r\nFitness Instructor (Orthos). \r\nSwimming instructor for specials groups (Univesidad de Barcelona). \r\nSwimming instructor (Federación Española de Natación). \r\n\r\nDegree in Psychology . Univesidad de Barcelona (Spain)	\r\nMasters (teacher training). Universidad Complutense de Madrid (Spain) ',	0,	1),
(108,	105,	'shop_vendor',	'Hi my name is Veena Gollop and I am a mobile personal trainer with Fitness Inside Out. \r\n\r\nAs an Exercise Scientist / Fitness Consultant / Personal Trainer, I am committed to providing a comprehensive, healthy lifestyle promoting service. My passion for life allows me to guide all sorts of people to achieve their complete fitness potential. My training sessions are designed to be enjoyable, effective, and easily incorporated intomy clients’ already hectic lifestyles. \r\n\r\nMy professional experiences include over 12 years working at a variety of fitness centres, personal training studios, rehabilitation clinics and sporting complexes situated between Sydney and Brisbane. Goals achieved by my clients include weight management, pain management, recovery from injury and illness, sporting aspirations from the novice to the elite, and enhancement of lifestyle from improved overall well being. Let’s get your goals happening now! \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat Veena’s clients say: \r\n\r\n\r\n“Veena Gollop has been my personal trainer for about 8 years. After going to the gym &amp; training with a few other personal trainers, in order to lose weight, get fitter &amp; maintain good health as a middle-aged woman, Veena was the only trainer who understood my needs &amp; concerns, while making me feel good about myself. She has always been polite, good-humoured &amp; professional, as well as very reliable, punctual &amp;, if necessary, flexible in her session times, in order to suit me. \r\n\r\nVeena is highly skilled &amp; motivated &amp; takes a holistic approach to good health &amp; fitness. As she has been my trainer for 8 years, it is clear that I have found her training sessions to be of great benefit to me &amp; have also found her to be a warm &amp; caring person. \r\n\r\nI would recommend Veena as a personal trainer to anyone.” \r\n\r\nVivian – Vaucluse \r\n\r\nVeena has been my personal trainer for 2 years now. With her expertise and experience, she has tailored training to suit my needs, particularly as I have had sport injuries in the past. Veena makes me feel comfortable during our sessions, whilst making it fun and inspiring. I was quite self conscious, but now am confident and proud of my achievements. \r\n\r\nGabriella – Surry Hills \r\n\r\nVeena has a friendly approach and genuine interest in helping me achieve my goals. She monitors progress through regular assessments. In our first 6 months I significantly strengthened and toned my upper arms and stomach – areas I had previously worked out, but with no results. My sessions have been personalised and refined to suit my needs. \r\n\r\nHer willingness to explain and educate me as to how my body works and why I am training the way I am, helps me stay motivated. It also makes me confident to make wise choices when I’m on my own. She pushes me because she knows my capabilities and this is further encouraging because I realise I can achieve so much. \r\n\r\nRaynuha – Elizabeth Bay \r\n\r\n\r\nSuburbs \r\n------------- \r\n\r\nBondi, Double Bay, Rushcutters Bay, Paddington, City, Potts Point, Darlinghurst, Rose Bay, Maroubra, Bronte, Clovelly,Maroubra, Alexandria, Zetland, Roseberry, Little Bay, Botany, City CBD, Mascot, Randwick, KensingtonMosman, Cremorne, Neutral Bay, Crows next, Cammeray, Greenwich, Milsons Point, North Sydney \r\n\r\n\r\nEducation \r\n--------------- \r\n\r\nWollongong University \r\n\r\n\r\nQualifications \r\n--------------------- \r\n\r\nDegree Human Movement \r\nCertificate IV in Fitness (Personal Trainer) \r\nCertificate III in Fitness (Gym Instructor) \r\nCertified Punch Fit Boxing instructor \r\nSenior First Aid \r\nCertified MediBall Instructor - Australian School of Health &amp; Sports Science \r\nRegistered &amp; Insured Fitness Australia ',	0,	1),
(109,	106,	'shop_vendor',	'PERSONAL TRAINING &amp; SMALL GROUPS\r\n\r\nA summer body is made in WINTER, so start your fitness and health regime NOW!!\r\n\r\nHi my name is Natalie and I\'m a personal trainer around the Eastern Suburbs.\r\n\r\nMy passion is to inspire my clients, encourage them to reach their personal goals and to help educate them on living a healthy lifestyle.\r\n\r\nAll of my sessions are tailored to the indivdual needs of each and every client, whether it be weight loss, toning, strength, fitness, core strengthening.\r\n\r\nExercising outdoors instead of at the gym is the key to physical and emotional wellbeing.\r\n\r\nDO YOU......\r\n\r\n*** Need MOTIVATION to train?\r\n\r\n*** Need INSPIRATION to help you achieve your fitness goals?\r\n\r\n*** Want RESULTS?\r\n\r\nIf the answer is YES then call Natalie today!\r\n\r\nSpecializing in..........\r\n\r\nOne on One Personal Training (30 mins, 45 mins or 1 hour sessions)\r\n\r\nSmall Group sessions with friends or work colleagues.',	0,	1),
(110,	107,	'shop_vendor',	'Idealbody4life –Personal Training introducing unique personal training plans for clients over 55 years young. Our personal trainers have training and experience specialising in helping clients over 55 to achieve their unique fitness and health goals. As we get older our training goals and priorities must change to make sure that:\r\n\r\n1. Workout plan helps to reduce health risks, such as osteoporosis and heart disease, while taking into account health history\r\n\r\n2. Workout Plan must weed out high impact and high risk exercises due to the fact that as we get older recovery tends to slow down, while our joints are more susceptible to injury. Most high impact and high risk of injury exercises can be replaced with a safer lower impact exercise that will achieve the same result.\r\n\r\nIdealbody4life Personal Training workout plans take all of this aspect into account when planning workouts for our clients, in order to not just achieve fitness and health goals but to do so safely with a minimum risk of injury.\r\n\r\nIdealbody4life Personal Training services are very convenient to use as we come directly to your location, providing you with all the necessary equipment for each unique workout!',	0,	1),
(111,	108,	'shop_vendor',	'Exercise and living a healthly lifestyle are KEY to a fullfilling and happy life!\r\n\r\nMore than just your average personal trainer - I have an extensive knowledge of human anatomy, functional fitness and rehabilitation. What makes this more holistic, is my passion for a healthy nutrition and living a healthy lifestyle!\r\n\r\nWith sessions starting from as little as $20 - what more are you waiting for?\r\n\r\nGroup sessions include no more than 6 people per group and sessions never the same, this could be you chance to get fit and have fun along the way!\r\nSessions last 45 minutes and include everything from functional work, battle ropes, body weight exercises, paired competitions, strength work, boxing, kick boxing and much more!\r\n\r\nIndividual sessions include a FREE prescreening (lasting approx 30-40 mins), with a follow up baseline testing and tailored individual program and nutrition advice/planning. Baseline testing includes objective measures, anthropometric data, flexibility, range of motion,\r\naerobic and strength tests, postural analysis, gait analysis, core/abdominal strength,\r\nbalance and coordination functional tests diet and nutrition and much, much more…',	0,	1),
(114,	111,	'shop_vendor',	'My name is Sonia, I\'ve been doing sport for more than 20 years with the same passion and same reason: it transforms people life througth exercise.\r\nIt brings confidence, strength, wellness, muscle and it boosts your energy.\r\n\r\nYou can be fit too! It \'s about one step, so Book now!\r\n\r\nand Please be my guest for your first session and get also a free initial consultation.\r\nLet\'s workout together and also have a fun.\r\n\r\nI offer my indoor service in our boutique at 115-117 Anzac Parade, room 4, Kensington and my mobile Outdoor Personal training in Eastern Suburb.',	0,	1),
(116,	113,	'pa_location',	'',	0,	31),
(118,	115,	'shop_vendor',	'Established by Simon Borg Olivier &amp; Bianca Machliss  in 1984, Yoga Synergy is one of Sydney’s largest and most respected yoga schools. We are conveniently located at Bondi Junction, North Bondi, Newtown and Surry Hills.\r\n\r\nOur aim at Yoga Synergy\r\nBy embarking on the path of yoga, one enters a journey to open the heart and clear the mind, to discover our true being, which is the ultimate reality – the transcendental self, the <em>atma</em> or the divine.\r\nWe are essentially the same humanity as 5000 years ago, so the insights that were discovered then, in the name of yoga are still valid today. Yoga as the union of body mind and spirit leads one to freedom, compassion and harmony.\r\nOur aim at Yoga Synergy is to teach the ancient art of yoga in a safe, fun and intelligent way. We teach students to practice responsively (not automatically) so that each practice fulfils the physical, mental, emotional and spiritual needs of the individual practitioner, enhancing life force, energy and vitality.',	0,	1),
(119,	116,	'shop_vendor',	'<strong>AT CFS WHAT DO WE BELIEVE IN?</strong>\r\nAt CFS what do we believe in? We believe in fundamental training and nutrition principles, we believe in never stop learning, never sit still, no one person is greater than the sum of all working together, we train for athletic performance not the pursuit of aesthetics, train for an objective, the mind is more powerful than the body, be responsible for you and your actions...but the most important aspect of CFS is that we are a community that is stronger together.',	0,	0),
(120,	117,	'shop_vendor',	'StarFit - Nutrition &amp; Fitness\r\nDescription\r\nStarFit offers personalised nutrition advice and nutrition workshops from a qualified Dietitian!\r\n\r\nContact us today for more info!',	0,	0),
(121,	118,	'shop_vendor',	'CrossFit 2036 | Forging YOUR Elite Fitness in South Sydney\r\n\r\nLocated just minutes south of the Sydney CBD, CrossFit 2036 is a special kind of personal and group training facility.\r\n\r\nWe use functional exercise, plyometrics, conditioning training, Olympic style weightlifting, powerlifting, gymnastics, running, jumping, rowing and throwing to help people reach their goals and maximize their health.\r\n\r\nWe understand that our community is diverse in their experience and day-to-day lives and our program is constructed with this principle in mind. Our approach to program design allows anyone to achieve results. The workouts are constantly varied, scalable and the results are dramatic.\r\n\r\nOur community is one of a kind and full of likeminded individuals offering friendly motivation and support. It’s something we are very proud of.\r\n\r\nWe train every age and every need including but not limited to weightlifters, marathoners, triathletes, gymnasts, the injured, first timers, professional athletes, and the very busy professional.',	0,	0),
(122,	119,	'shop_vendor',	'<strong>Getting Started</strong>\r\nNew to CrossFit?\r\nStep 1 - Come and Try\r\nCrossFit is such a comprehensive way to fitness and better wellbeing it is difficult to explain so we offer a free trial session so you can check it out. We’ll explain what it’s about, run through some CrossFit basics on movement, mobility and nutrition and answer your questions.\r\nAfter you’ve done your trial session you can join straight away (experienced CrossFitters) or jump into the Fundamentals Course and begin your path to fitness and wellness.\r\nSimply call or email us so we can direct you to the most appropriate class day and time for your free session!\r\nStep 2 - Fundamentals Course (including 2-weeks membership)\r\nIf, after your free session, you would like to join us, then you will need to complete our Fundamentals Course consisting of two educational sessions within a 2-week membership. We will cover the nine fundamental movements and will brief you on nutrition, mobility, rest and CrossFit lingo.\r\nYou will learn the following fundamental movements:\r\n\r\n	Squat\r\n	Front squat\r\n	Overhead squat\r\n	Strict press\r\n	Push press\r\n	Push jerk\r\n	Deadlift\r\n	Sumo deadlift high-pull\r\n	Med-ball clean\r\n\r\nFundamentals sessions are run two mornings and three evenings per week. If timing is a problem, call and we may be able to make other arrangements.\r\nOnce you have completed the Fundamentals Course you are free to continue your membership and attend any of the group sessions and open gym sessions.',	0,	0),
(123,	120,	'shop_vendor',	'There are so many CrossFit boxes to choose from these days, so what makes our box the one for you?\r\nYou mean apart from the fact that we were one of the first to open in Sydney? :)\r\nCrossFit is about a bunch of likeminded people getting together for awesome workouts day after day.\r\nThere\'s no expectations on performance, there\'s no dress code, there\'s no pretention, there is only the team spirit of everyone taking on the same tough workout and giving it their best.\r\nUnfortunately the image of CrossFit can be portrayed as \"hardcore\" or \"extreme\", but in reality, that is only applicable to about 5% of the CrossFit population. At CrossFit Kensington, we cater to the 95% of people who just want to get fit and lose weight in a fun, supportive, safe and professional environment.\r\nOur classes will ensure you;\r\n\r\n\r\n	Increase your aerobic fitness\r\n	Increase your anaerobic fitness\r\n	Increase your strength\r\n	Decrease your body fat\r\n	Improve your stamina\r\n	Improve your flexibility\r\n	Improve your core strength\r\n	Improve your coordination\r\n	Increase your power\r\n	Increase your speed\r\n	Improve your balance\r\n\r\nDoes your current fitness regimen does that?\r\n\r\nOur CrossFit box is nothing like a traditional gym. All classes are instructed as group personal training lessons at a fraction of the cost of 1on1 personal training.\r\nIf you are thinking \"That sounds awesome, but I don\'t know if I am fit enough for it\" then please put that thought out of your head, because nobody has to be fit to commence any exercise program!\r\nWe cater to all fitness levels, from absolute beginners to seasoned athletes and all workouts can be scaled either by weight or movement or both, so the only thing I can say is give it a try and you will never look back!',	0,	0),
(124,	121,	'shop_vendor',	'<strong>Getting Started</strong>\r\nWant to give CrossFit a try? Come along to one of our free trial classes every Tuesday and Thursday night at 7:15pm.\r\n\r\nFrom there to join up we put all new members through the Starter On-Ramp program. This is a specialised 4 week program designed to teach you the foundational movements of CrossFit.',	0,	0),
(125,	122,	'shop_vendor',	'ABOUT\r\nThe CrossFit Bare difference\r\n\r\nWe are not a gym!\r\n\r\nSure we throw weights around, run, jump, sweat, strain, grunt and groan like a regular gym. But at CrossFit Bare, we do it together.\r\n\r\nAt Bare you’re a person: not a member. You’ll get more handshakes, high fives, fist pumps and g’days than at a BBQ with old friends.\r\n\r\nYou’ll work hard, so hard you may feel like giving up. But someone will always be there to pick you up and help you through.\r\n\r\nYou’ll do things you love and things you hate. You’ll always have a coach, sometimes a room full of them, and some day you may do some coaching of your own.\r\n\r\nYou’ll do CrossFit. A functional fitness program and a damn good one. CrossFit Bare however, is more than that. It’s an empowering lifestyle program. The workouts are just as challenging as any other gym, often much more so, but the Bare difference is its community.\r\n\r\nWe’re a family. We train together, grow together and share in both our highs and lows.\r\n\r\nJoining the Bare community, you’ll see more changes then you could ever dream of at a normal gym. You’ll lose weight, gain lean muscle, boost your energy and get fitter, stronger, faster and more mobile than you ever thought possible. But best of all you’ll change your mindset and gain confidence and a bunch of new friends along the way.\r\n\r\nTake the challenge and Bare it all.',	0,	0),
(126,	123,	'shop_vendor',	'',	0,	0),
(127,	124,	'shop_vendor',	'Mettle Nation CrossFit in Inner Sydney is minutes away from busy Sydney CBD NSW Australia. Located on the famous Riley Street in Darlinghurst we at Mettle Nation CrossFit take pride in delivering a premium CrossFit experience to Sydneysiders. With the use of various strength and conditioning parameters such as Olympic Weightlifting, power lifting and other resistance training protocols, calisthenics and bar, ring &amp; floor gymnastics and of course more traditional cardio based exercises like running, skipping, medicine ball work, rowing and stationary bikes we aspire to take your training to a new level!',	0,	0),
(128,	125,	'shop_vendor',	'What is Zumba® Fitness?\r\nZumba® fitness is like no other workout you will ever experience!\r\nThe Zumba® programme was created in the 1990s by Colombian native Alberto \"Beto\" Perez, a celebrity fitness trainer and choreographer for international pop superstars. Inspired by the traditional cumbia, salsa, samba and merengue music he grew up with, Beto paired his favourite pulsating Latin rhythms with the red-hot international dance steps that his clients loved and created the Zumba® Fitness-Party.\r\n \r\nSince Beto brought the Zumba® Fitness programme to the U.S. in 1999, it has become a huge fitness success, with people of all ages falling in love with its infectious music, easy-to-follow dance moves and body-beautifying benefits.',	0,	0),
(129,	126,	'shop_vendor',	'Our studio is a friendly environment where everyone gets a personalised attention.\r\n\r\nWe are a smaller studio facility compared to other giant gyms, at just over 75 square metres, so our service is very personal.\r\n\r\nMost of our class sizes vary between 6 to 10 members at any one time, so you’ll never get lost in the crowd.',	0,	2),
(130,	127,	'shop_vendor',	'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Hi, I’m John Hagar owner of In Motion Personal Training at Randwick. Since starting in the health and fitness industry in 2003 as a personal trainer. I’ve worked with hundreds of people to achieve their dreams and goals.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Through the years I have continued to update my knowledge to stay at the leading edge of health and fitness education and have expertise in areas as diverse as. Advanced Resistance Training, Advanced Aerobic Conditioning, Nutrition, Core Conditioning, Myofascial Massage, Pre &amp; Post Natal Training.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In addition to all of my formal qualifications, I am an accomplished sportsman and have more recently trained in kickboxing and Jiu Jitsu.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I have been very successful in applying some of these techniques in my personal training and group fitness programs.</p>',	0,	2),
(131,	128,	'product_cat',	'',	0,	5),
