(153,	144,	'shop_vendor',	'Bondi Beach is arguably one of Australia’s most popular and iconic beaches.  It is certainly Australia’s best-known beach.\r\nFrom lazing in the sun, exercising on the beach, swimming in the surf, enjoying a great meal or just soaking up the atmosphere, there is something for everyone at Bondi Beach.\r\nThere is even a community group that promotes health, fitness and nutrition through the use of street workout and calisthenics techniques.\r\nThat group is the <strong>Bondi Beach BAR Brutes.</strong>\r\nThe <strong>Bondi Beach BAR Brutes</strong> was officially formed in September 2012, from amongst a group of committed fitness enthusiasts who regularly use the outdoor gym at <strong>North Bondi Beach</strong>.\r\nIt is a community organization and Sporting Club with the following goals:\r\n\r\nPromoting health and fitness in the outdoors without the use of technology;\r\nInspiring and motivating all people to have fun through exercise and improve their health through good nutrition;\r\nEncouraging individual achievement and community spirit.\r\n\r\nA small Management Group, headed by passionate founder Stan Veniaminov, lead the <strong>Bondi Beach BAR Brutes</strong> team.\r\nThe Bondi Beach BAR Brutes embrace the diverse and health conscious Bondi scene with a wide range of cultural groups, lifestyles and age ranges reflected in their membership.  They complement the overall Bondi Beach atmosphere and welcome all community members to participate in and enjoy the Outdoor Gym at North Bondi Beach.\r\nThe <strong>Bondi Beach BAR Brutes</strong> is part of a growing international network of street workout and calisthenics groups focused on promoting a high quality of life through exercise and nutrition for all age groups.  Social media, particularly Facebook, You Tube and the internet play a vital role in providing strong communication likes for these groups to share stories, training tips and exercise videos.\r\nWomen and young people are particularly encouraged and strongly supported.\r\nTo encourage increased community participation in fitness, the <strong>Bondi Beach BAR Brutes</strong> hold Competitions at the outdoor gym on the <strong>first Sunday of every month</strong>.\r\nParticipation in Monthly Competitions is FREE.',	0,	1),
